GETTING THE SOURCE CODE
=======================

The code is hosted at github::

  http://github.com/k0001/mediasancion

You can clone it from::

  git://github.com/k0001/mediasancion.git


INSTALL
=======

1. Setup and activate a virutalenv environment::

    virtualenv ~/ve/MS --python=/usr/bin/python2.5
    source ~/ve/MS/bin/activate

2. Install libxml2 inside the virtualenv (if not globablly available)::

    cd /tmp
    wget ftp://ftp.xmlsoft.org/libxml2/libxml2-2.7.3.tar.gz
    tar xzf libxml2-2.7.3.tar.gz
    cd libxml2-2.7.3
    ./configure --prefix=$VIRTUAL_ENV --with-threads --with-history --with-python=$VIRTUAL_ENV/bin/python
    make
    make install

3. Install Python requirements using pip::

    pip install -r pip-requirements.txt


